<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="231" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="2.[136,1452,1718,2069]" pageId="2" pageNumber="231">
Differing from 
<taxonomicName box="[319,606,1718,1744]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Trypetheliaceae" genus="Astrothelium" kingdom="Fungi" order="Trypetheliales" pageId="2" pageNumber="231" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="flavoduplex">
<emphasis box="[319,606,1718,1744]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="231">Astrothelium flavoduplex</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having trypethelioid ascomata without forming pseudostroma, being solitary and with a conspicuous yellow pruina, as well as the IKI+ blue ascospores.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
